<p>NIMS Introduces wireless capsule endoscopy</p>
<p>THIRUVANANTHAPURAM: NIMS medicity has introduced wireless capsule endoscopy, a new diagnostic tool for the detection of small bowel disease non-invasively.</p>
<p>This technique does not require insertion of endoscope through the mouth.</p>
<p>Instead of lying down still on an examination table during the exam, patients can walk after the ingestion of the pill.</p>
<p>People while using wireless endoscopy can walk, sit and even return to normal work while the capsules are recording images.</p>
<p>It is also disposable and therefore comfortable to patients.</p>
